summary: This document is an AT&T telephone call detail record for the number (561) 333-0180, covering the period from January 1, 2002, to December 31, 2006. It was produced in response to a subpoena (Matter ID: 2750179) and contains thousands of call entries showing dates, times, durations, and call codes, likely used for investigative purposes in the Epstein case.
keyFacts: AT&T produced telephone records for the number (561) 333-0180 covering a five-year period from 2002 to 2006.
The records were created on June 18, 2019, in response to a subpoena (Matter ID: 2750179) from law enforcement.
The document contains over 4,100 individual call detail entries, showing call dates, times (UTC), durations, and various call codes.
The records are stored and provided in UTC time, but the query was run using Eastern Time Zone.
The document is part of the evidence produced to the Southern District of New York (SDNY) in the Epstein investigation.
